text.section:
Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, a heading shall be printed at the top of the ballot and shall contain, in the following order:
the words "Official Ballot";
the type of election, i.e., regular or special, primary or general, and any other information required to identify the election being held;
the date of the election;
the words "State of Maryland" and the name of the county;
in a primary election, the name of the political party or the words "nonpartisan ballot", as applicable, for which the ballot or a portion of the ballot is to be used; and
if more than one ballot style will be used in the county in the election, the ballot style indicator.
